wing like bract attached to fruit

Acer pseudoplatanus,Sycamore is easily distinguished by its more prominant lobing (5 lobes) of the leaves as well as its pendulus flowers and fruit wings being closer together (approx. right angled). Overall a taller tree. Petioles don't have milky juice.
A small tree, sometimes shrub. Field maple leaves are deeply palmate (3 or 5) lobed. The petioles have milky juice. The fruit are distinct paired "helicopters" or "keys", which spread horizontally.
